1 NOTE Rev. Constantine Cyran was ordained a Catholic Priest in 1919. He then went to Rome, Italy, where he earned an STD degree from the Gregorian University in 1921 and a doctorate of Philosophy the next y
2 CONC ear. He began a long teaching career in 1922 at his alma Mater, SS. Cyril and Methodius Seminary and St. Mary College in Orchard Lake Michigan. During that time he taught most of the core courses in t
2 CONC he seminary. He was ill for a long time and was retired before his death at the age of 73.
